#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:5
msgid ""
"# Gnome ## Gnome Traits - - - Your gnome character has certain "
"characteristics in common with all other gnomes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Ability Score Increase.** Your Intelligence score increases by 2. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Age.** Gnomes mature at the same rate humans do, and most are expected to "
"settle down into an adult life by around age 40. They can live 350 to almost "
"500 years. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Alignment.** Gnomes are most often good. Those who tend toward law are "
"sages, engineers, researchers, scholars, investigators, or inventors. Those "
"who tend toward chaos are minstrels, tricksters, wanderers, or fanciful "
"jewelers. Gnomes are good-hearted, and even the tricksters among them are "
"more playful than vicious. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Size.** Gnomes are between 3 and 4 feet tall and average about 40 "
"pounds. Your size is Small.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Speed.** Your base walking speed is 25 feet. Darkvision. Accustomed to "
"life underground, you have superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You "
"can see in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light, and "
"in darkness as if it were dim light. You can’t discern color in darkness, "
"only shades of gray. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Gnome Cunning.** You have advantage on all Intelligence, Wisdom, and "
"Charisma saving throws against magic. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Languages.** You can speak, read, and write Common and Gnomish. The "
"Gnomish language, which uses the Dwarvish script, is renowned for its "
"technical treatises and its catalogs of knowledge about the natural "
"world. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:22
msgid ""
"## Rock Gnome As a rock gnome, you have a natural inventiveness and "
"hardiness beyond that of other gnomes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Ability Score Increase.** Your Constitution score increases by 1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Artificer’s Lore.** Whenever you make an Intelligence (History) check "
"related to magic items, alchemical objects, or technological devices, you "
"can add twice your proficiency bonus, instead of any proficiency bonus you "
"normally apply. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Tinker.** You have proficiency with artisan’s tools (tinker’s "
"tools). Using those tools, you can spend 1 hour and 10 gp worth of materials "
"to construct a Tiny clockwork device (AC 5, 1 hp). The device ceases to "
"function after 24 hours (unless you spend 1 hour repairing it to keep the "
"device functioning), or when you use your action to dismantle it; at that "
"time, you can reclaim the materials used to create it. You can have up to "
"three such devices active at a time. \n"
"When you create a device, choose one of the following options: \n"
">**Clockwork Toy.** This toy is a clockwork animal, monster, or person, such "
"as a frog, mouse, bird, dragon, or soldier. When placed on the ground, the "
"toy moves 5 feet across the ground on each of your turns in a random "
"direction. It makes noises as appropriate to the creature it represents. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:32
msgid ""
">**Fire Starter.** The device produces a miniature flame, which you can use "
"to light a candle, torch, or campfire. Using the device requires your "
"action."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/races/gnome.md:33
msgid ""
">**Music Box.** When opened, this music box plays a single song at a "
"moderate volume. The box stops playing when it reaches the song’s end or "
"when it is closed."
msgstr ""
